{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.26",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 26,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 26 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:1",
      "text": "As snow in summer, and rain in harvest, so glory is not seemly for a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:2",
      "text": "As a bird flying to other places, and a sparrow going here or there: so a curse uttered without cause shall come upon a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:3",
      "text": "A whip for a horse, and a snaffle for an ass, and a rod for the back of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:4",
      "text": "Answer not a fool according to his folly, lest thou be made like him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:5",
      "text": "Answer a fool according to his folly, lest he imagine himself to be wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:6",
      "text": "He that sendeth words by a foolish messenger, is lame of feet and drinketh iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:7",
      "text": "As a lame man hath fair legs in vain: so a parable is unseemly in the mouth of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:8",
      "text": "As he that casteth a stone into the heap of Mercury: so is he that giveth honour to a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:9",
      "text": "As if a thorn should grow in the hand of a drunkard: so is a parable in the mouth of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:10",
      "text": "Judgment determineth causes: and he that putteth a fool to silence, appeaseth anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:11",
      "text": "As a dog that returneth to his vomit, so is the fool that repeateth his folly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:12",
      "text": "Hast thou seen a man wise in his own conceit? there shall be more hope of a fool than of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:13",
      "text": "The slothful man saith: There is a lion in the way, and a lioness in the roads.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:14",
      "text": "As the door turneth upon its hinges, so doth the slothful upon his bed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:15",
      "text": "The slothful hideth his hand under his armpit, and it grieveth him to turn it to his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:16",
      "text": "The sluggard is wiser in his own conceit, than seven men that speak sentences.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:17",
      "text": "As he that taketh a dog by the ears, so is he that passeth by in anger, and meddleth with another man's quarrel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:18",
      "text": "As he is guilty that shooteth arrows, and lances unto death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:19",
      "text": "So is the man that hurteth his friend deceitfully: and when he is taken, saith: I did it in jest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:20",
      "text": "When the wood faileth, the fire shall go out: and when the talebearer is taken away, contentions shall cease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:21",
      "text": "As coals are to burning coals, and wood to fire, so an angry man stirreth up strife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:22",
      "text": "The words of a talebearer are as it were simple, but they reach to the innermost parts of the belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:23",
      "text": "Swelling lips joined with a corrupt heart, are like an earthern vessel adorned with silver dross.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:24",
      "text": "An enemy is known by his lips, when in his heart he entertaineth deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:25",
      "text": "When he shall speak low, trust him not: because there are seven mischiefs in his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:26",
      "text": "He that covereth hatred deceitfully, his malice shall be laid open in the public assembly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:27",
      "text": "He that diggeth a pit, shall fall into it: and he that rolleth a stone, it shall return to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.26.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:28",
      "text": "A deceitful tongue loveth not truth: and a slippery mouth worketh ruin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
